==Description== <!--T:2-->

<!--T:5-->
The [[Image:Sketcher_SelectConstraints.svg|24px]] [[Sketcher_SelectConstraints|Sketcher SelectConstraints]] tool
selects the constraints associated with sketch elements.

==Usage== <!--T:3-->

<!--T:6-->
# Select one or more sketch elements.
# There are several ways to invoke the tool:
#* Press the {{Button|[[File:Sketcher_SelectConstraints.svg|16px]] [[Sketcher_SelectConstraints|Select Associated Constraints]]}} button.
#* Select the {{MenuCommand|Sketch → Visual Helpers → [[File:Sketcher_SelectConstraints.svg|16px]] Select Associated Constraints}} option from the menu.
#* {{Version|1.0}}: Right-click in the [[3D_View|3D View]] and select the {{MenuCommand|[[Image:Sketcher_SelectConstraints.svg|16px]] Select Associated Constraints}} option from the context menu.
#* Right-click in the '''Elements''' section of the [[Sketcher_Dialog|Sketcher Dialog]] and select the {{MenuCommand|[[Image:Sketcher_SelectConstraints.svg|16px]] Select Constraints}} option from the context menu.
#* Use the keyboard shortcut: {{KEY|Z}} then {{KEY|K}}.
# The associated constraints are selected.
# Optionally click in an empty area in the [[3D_View|3D View]] to clear the selection.


